\begin_inset Formula $x(z+v)=x(z)+x'(z)\frac{v}{1!}+x''(z)\frac{v^{2}}{2!}+x'''(z)\frac{v^{3}}{3!}+\cdots$
\end_inset

.
 In the notation of Taylor, 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\dot{x}}{\dot{z}}$
\end_inset

 is the first derivative of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

